Sales Analytics brings the power of Analytics to Sales Cloud on any device that supports Analytics. With intuitive visualizations based on your Salesforce data, Sales Analytics lets you move from insight to action quickly and helps you turn data into smarter sales.

About Sales Analytics
Learn the benefits of Sales Analytics before you create and use the app to explore your Sales Cloud data.
Sales Analytics Prebuilt Dashboards, Lenses, and Datasets
Sales Analytics includes a prebuilt dashboard, lenses, and dataset to accelerate your data exploration.
Set Up Permissions for the Sales Analytics
Set up your organization to use the Sales Analytics by enabling CRM Analytics and assigning permission sets to users.
Create and Share Sales Analytics
Follow these steps to create Sales Analytics and start uncovering the value of your Salesforce data.
Customize Sales Analytics with the Configuration Wizard
Create Sales Analytics with the configuration wizard so the app reflects how your company prefers to view Salesforce data.
Delete Sales Analytics
Delete apps to start app creation all over or to get rid of apps you no longer use.
Upgrade Sales Analytics App
Take advantage of the latest Sales Analytics features by upgrading your app when we release a new version.
Reconfigure Sales Analytics
To restore deleted or altered dashboards or change wizard settings, reconfigure an existing app.

You can achieve collaborative forecasting and quotas data in Sales Analytics, schedule the Sales Analytics data sync and dataflow, integrate Sales Analytics with Salesforce, understand Sales Analytics limitations, get to know Sales Analytics data terminology.
